cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks related to radiometric calibration and image processing, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning models also suggests the machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of multi-scale pyramid and histogram layers, which are commonly used in deep learning for image processing and feature extraction, indicating the machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method to image deblurring, which falls under the image processing (cs.IR) sub-category.
